The [[Bayer designation]] ξ Lupi ('''Xi Lupi''') is shared by two [[star system]]s in the [[constellation]] [[Lupus (constellation)|Lupus]]: *[[Xi1 Lupi|ξ<sup>1</sup> Lupi]] (HD 142629) *[[Xi2 Lupi|ξ<sup>2</sup> Lupi]] (HD 142630)
Listed in the [[Washington Double Star Catalog]] as WDS J15569-3358, this [[double star]] most likely forms a wide [[binary star]] system.<ref name=Eggleton2008/> As of [[Epoch (astronomy)|epoch]] 2004.38, the pair had an [[angular separation]] of {{Val|10.254|0.016|u=arc seconds}} along a [[position angle]] of {{Val|49.21|0.02|u=°}}. The difference in [[visual magnitude]] between the two stars is {{Val|0.515|0.003}}.<ref name=Sinachopoulos2007/>
